# Design System Standards

## CSS Modules — Mandatory

All styling uses CSS Modules (`.module.css`). NEVER use inline styles or `style={{ }}` props.

```
ComponentName/
├── ComponentName.tsx
├── ComponentName.module.css    # scoped styles
└── index.ts
```

- Each component has its own `.module.css`. Styles are NOT shared between modules.
- Reusable values live in tokens (`var(--ds-*)`) or in `styles/common.css`.
- Use `composes:` for composing CSS classes within the same module.

```typescript
// FORBIDDEN — inline styles
<div style={{ color: '#3b82f6', padding: '16px' }}>
<div style={{ backgroundColor: 'var(--ds-color-bg-base)' }}>

// REQUIRED — CSS Modules
import styles from './Card.module.css';
<div className={styles.container}>
```

## Design Tokens — Enforced by Stylelint

All visual values come from tokens. NEVER hardcode colors, spacing, typography, shadows, or ANY dimensional value.

Tokens live in `packages/ds/src/styles/tokens.css` and are consumed via CSS custom properties inside `.module.css` files.

**This is enforced by Stylelint** (`pnpm lint:css`). The linter will reject ANY hardcoded value in `.module.css` files.

## Colors

- ZERO hardcoded color values (`#hex`, `rgb()`, `hsl()`) in components.
- All colors reference token variables: `var(--ds-color-*)`.
- Semantic naming: `--ds-color-brand-primary`, `--ds-color-status-error`, not `--blue-500`.

## Typography

- All font sizes: `var(--ds-font-size-*)`.
- All font weights: `var(--ds-font-weight-*)`.
- All line heights: `var(--ds-line-height-*)`.
- All letter spacings: `var(--ds-letter-spacing-*)`.

## Spacing

- ALL spacing uses tokens: `var(--ds-spacing-*)`. Including zero → `var(--ds-spacing-0)`.
- No magic pixel numbers, no raw `rem`, `em`, `px` values.

## Sizing

- Component sizes use tokens: `var(--ds-size-*)`.
- Layout values use tokens: `var(--ds-layout-*)`, `var(--ds-size-full)`, `var(--ds-size-screen-h)`.
- No hardcoded `100%`, `100vh`, `240px`, etc. — use the corresponding token.

## Borders

- Border widths: `var(--ds-border-width-*)`.
- Border radii: `var(--ds-radius-*)`.
- Use longhand properties (`border-width`, `border-style`, `border-color`) instead of shorthand to keep each value tokenized.

## Opacity

- Use `var(--ds-opacity-disabled)` instead of raw `0.5`.

## Animations

- Duration tokens: `var(--ds-duration-*)`.
- Easing tokens: `var(--ds-easing-*)`.

## Available Token Categories

| Category | Prefix | Example |
|----------|--------|---------|
| Colors | `--ds-color-*` | `--ds-color-brand-primary` |
| Spacing | `--ds-spacing-*` | `--ds-spacing-4` |
| Typography | `--ds-font-*` | `--ds-font-size-lg` |
| Line heights | `--ds-line-height-*` | `--ds-line-height-normal` |
| Letter spacing | `--ds-letter-spacing-*` | `--ds-letter-spacing-tight` |
| Border widths | `--ds-border-width-*` | `--ds-border-width-thin` |
| Radii | `--ds-radius-*` | `--ds-radius-md` |
| Shadows | `--ds-shadow-*` | `--ds-shadow-md` |
| Opacity | `--ds-opacity-*` | `--ds-opacity-disabled` |
| Sizes | `--ds-size-*` | `--ds-size-full`, `--ds-size-icon-md` |
| Layout | `--ds-layout-*` | `--ds-layout-max-width-md` |
| Duration | `--ds-duration-*` | `--ds-duration-normal` |
| Easing | `--ds-easing-*` | `--ds-easing-default` |

## Text & i18n

All user-visible text MUST come from i18n. No hardcoded strings in components.

```typescript
// FORBIDDEN
<h1>Welcome to Dashboard</h1>

// REQUIRED
import { useTranslation } from 'react-i18next';
const { t } = useTranslation();
<h1>{t('dashboard.welcome')}</h1>
```

## Generic Components

- Build a library of generic, composable UI components.
- Generic components live at the design system level, not inside features.
- Components accept tokens/variants via props, resolved to CSS classes — never inline styles.
- Every generic component must work standalone without feature-specific context.

## Storybook

- Every atom, molecule, and generic component MUST have a Storybook story.
- Stories document all variants, states, and edge cases.
- Stories serve as living documentation and visual regression test targets.
- Story file: `<ComponentName>.stories.tsx` colocated with the component.

```typescript
// Button.stories.tsx
import type { Meta, StoryObj } from '@storybook/react';
import { Button } from './Button';

const meta: Meta<typeof Button> = {
  component: Button,
  title: 'Atoms/Button',
};

export default meta;
type Story = StoryObj<typeof Button>;

export const Primary: Story = { args: { label: 'Click me', variant: 'primary' } };
export const Secondary: Story = { args: { label: 'Cancel', variant: 'secondary' } };
```
